.TH SCALE\-GUINSTALL 1 "2026-07-03" "1.0.1" "Scale GUInstall"
.SH NAME
scale\-guinstall \- IBM Storage Scale Installation Toolkit GUI backend server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B scale\-guinstall
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B scale\-guinstall
starts the Flask backend server for Scale GUInstall, a web-based GUI
for the IBM Storage Scale Installation Toolkit
.RB ( spectrumscale ).
.PP
The server listens on
.B http://127.0.0.1:5001
(loopback only) and provides Server-Sent Event (SSE) streaming endpoints
that the GUI calls to execute
.B spectrumscale
commands and stream output back to the browser.
.PP
Open
.B Scale\-GUInstall.html
in a browser on the same machine, or tunnel the port from a remote
workstation using SSH (see
.B EXAMPLES
below).
.SH OPTIONS
.B scale\-guinstall
takes no command-line options.
The listening port can be overridden with the
.B PORT
environment variable.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PORT
Override the listening port (default:
.BR 5001 ).
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/lib/scale\-guinstall/scale\-server.py
The Flask application.
.TP
.B /usr/lib/scale\-guinstall/Scale\-GUInstall.html
The single-file web application. Open this in your browser.
.TP
.B /usr/lib/scale\-guinstall/venv/
Python virtual environment containing Flask, created during package
installation.
.TP
.B /usr/lib/systemd/system/scale\-guinstall.service
systemd unit file. The service is installed but not enabled by default.
.TP
.B /usr/share/doc/scale\-guinstall/README.md
Full documentation.
.TP
.B /usr/share/doc/scale\-guinstall/CHANGELOG.md
Release history.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Run in the foreground
.EX
scale\-guinstall
.EE
.SS Run as a persistent systemd service
.EX
sudo systemctl enable \-\-now scale\-guinstall
.EE
.SS Connect from a remote workstation via SSH tunnel
Forward the server port over SSH, then open
.B Scale\-GUInstall.html
locally:
.EX
# Interactive (tunnel closes when the terminal closes)
ssh \-L 5001:127.0.0.1:5001 user@installer\-node

# Background (stays open after the terminal exits)
ssh \-fNL 5001:127.0.0.1:5001 user@installer\-node
.EE
Leave the Backend URL in the GUI at
.BR http://127.0.0.1:5001 ;
the SSH tunnel forwards it transparently.
.SS Override the port
.EX
PORT=8080 scale\-guinstall
.EE
.SH SECURITY
The server binds to
.B 127.0.0.1
only and is not reachable from the network.
CORS is restricted to
.BR localhost ,
.BR 127.0.0.1 ,
and
.B file://
origins.
All executed commands are explicitly allowlisted; there is no generic
shell execution endpoint.
Credentials are transmitted via POST request bodies and never appear in
URLs or query strings.
.PP
Because the server executes privileged commands (via
.BR sudo ),
do not expose it to untrusted networks.
Use the SSH tunnel approach for remote access.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR spectrumscale (1),
.BR ssh (1),
.BR systemctl (1)
.PP
IBM Storage Scale documentation:
.I https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/storage-scale/6.0.1
.PP
